# categories seem to be additive, vanilla is ok with defining its own categories multiple times in files
# no regard taken to load order of vanilla files either
# categories correspond to a slider in the sound settings menu, except "Weapon" which is used for all the weapon sounds
# if not attached to the right category then no slider will control the volume, only the master slider
# the vast majority of vanilla sounds are in "Ambient", "Effects", or "Weapon", advisors go in "Voice"
# there's also a "Menu" which appears 3 times but has no sounds assigned to it anywhere

